cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with image analysis and deep learning techniques for segmentation of biological cells in microscopy images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel loss function and contour-aware weight map model, which are related to machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with microscopy images, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which can be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
